NNOOTTEESS
       The  PNG driver uses the Gd library (http://www.boutell.com/gd/) devel-
       oped by Boutell.Com, Inc. The Gd library in turn relies on libpng  (see
       the  libpng home page) and zlib (see the info-zip home page), all which
       needs to be installed for the PNG driver to work (it's worth it).


       Note that the PNG driver  is  limited  to  8bit  colors  when  compiled
       against  libgd1.x.  From libgd2.x onwards true color support is option-
       ally provided.


       The resolution of the _P_N_G raster map is defined by the map extents. Use
       _g_._r_e_g_i_o_n  _-_p to get the number of rows and cols and use the environment
       variables to set the PNG size.



